body: As of now execution providers can be linked only statically. We're working on dynamic linking as we speak. fyi @RyanUnderhill

ok thanks. How to use the added provider? Do I need to copy the libonnxruntime_providers.a and libonnxruntime_providers_x.a to the release folder? Do I need to modify the app code (CXXapi_sample.cc)? How to build the app (since there's dynamic link with libonnxruntime.so and static link with providers)?

Ok I see, the 'Using the execution provider' section. Looks like I need to modify the CXXapi_sample.cc. This looks weird to me, which execution provider to use should be decided by onnxruntime, not by application.

issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
This is related to https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/2818
I have followed the steps (https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/docs/AddingExecutionProvider.md) to add my provider (denoted "X" here). BTW the doc needs update:  OrtCreateCUDAExecutionProviderFactory() should be CreateExecutionProviderFactory_CUDA() I think.

My problem is that I generated the provider static lib, but I can't link it with either C_Api_Sample.cpp or CXX_Api_Sample.cpp. They have the same problem: undefined reference to `OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_X'

I do see this function as a mangled function in the static lib:
$ nm --demangle ~/onnxruntime/rel/lib/libonnxruntime_providers_x.a | grep OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_X
0000000000000000 T OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_X(OrtSessionOptions*)
If I don't use the demangle option:
0000000000000000 T _Z48OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_XP17OrtSessionOptions

For C_Api_Sample.cpp, I added this:
#include <x_provider_factory.h>
...
auto res = (OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_X(session_options));

I compile it with:
g++ -o Capi_sample C_Api_Sample.cpp -I ~/onnxruntime/rel/include -std=c++11 -L ~/onnxruntime/rel/lib -Wl,-Bstatic -lonnxruntime_providers_x -Wl,-Bdynamic -lonnxruntime
got error:
C_Api_Sample.cpp:(.text+0x109): undefined reference to `OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_X'

For CXX_Api_Sample.cpp I added this:
Ort::SessionOptions \*session_options;
Ort::ThrowOnError(OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_X((OrtSessionOptions*)session_options));
And got the same error:
CXX_Api_Sample.cpp:(.text+0x50): undefined reference to `OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_X'

body:
@pranavsharma any roadmap/project or possibly branch publicly available of this... i.e. potentially help out with the effort?

basically it would be nice to be able to use onnxruntime API (c/c++) to check whether a backend is available and then use it. since now if the library has not been compiled with a given backend, one cannot even check via API which backend is available (runtime)

This feature is being worked on in a private branch and not at a stage where it can be opened up for community contributions due to multiple conflicting internal pieces. Once we've achieved this for one execution provider, we can open it up to the community. Stay tuned!
